body:
### Link to the code that reproduces this issue

https://github.com/joulev/debug/tree/turbopack-next-font-declarations-missing

### To Reproduce

1. Clone the repo, install deps
2. `pnpm dev` → view the generated CSS file for Webpack behaviour (correct)
3. `pnpm dev --turbopack` → view the generated CSS file for Turbopack behaviour (incorrect)

### Current vs. Expected behavior

We have

```ts
import localFont from "next/font/local";

const font = localFont({
  src: [{ path: "./regular.woff2", weight: "normal", style: "normal" }],
  display: "swap",
  declarations: [{ prop: "size-adjust", value: "90%" }],
  adjustFontFallback: false,
});
```

Running the app with Webpack, the `{ prop: "size-adjust", value: "90%" }` works:

```css
/* pnpm dev */
@font-face {
    size-adjust: 90%;
    font-family: 'font';
    src: url(/_next/static/media/bf09337bba4146da.p.woff2) format('woff2');
    font-display: swap;
    font-weight: normal;
    font-style: normal;
}
```

Running the app with Turbopack, the declaration no longer works:

```css
/* pnpm dev --turbopack */
@font-face {
  font-family: font;
  src: url("../media/regular.p.eeec7ef5.woff2") format("woff2");
  font-display: swap;
  font-weight: normal;
  font-style: normal;
}
```

**Expected behaviour:** `localFont`'s `declarations` should work with Turbopack.

### Provide environment information

```bash
Operating System:
  Platform: linux
  Arch: x64
  Version: #35~22.04.1-Ubuntu SMP Mon May 26 18:08:30 UTC 2025
  Available memory (MB): 7945
  Available CPU cores: 2
Binaries:
  Node: 18.20.8
  npm: 10.8.2
  Yarn: 1.22.22
  pnpm: 10.11.0
Relevant Packages:
  next: 15.5.0 // Latest available version is detected (15.5.0).
  eslint-config-next: N/A
  react: 19.1.1
  react-dom: 19.1.1
  typescript: 5.9.2
Next.js Config:
  output: N/A
```

### Which area(s) are affected? (Select all that apply)

Font (next/font), Turbopack

### Which stage(s) are affected? (Select all that apply)

next dev (local), next build (local), Vercel (Deployed), Other (Deployed)

